==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Prosylogism
<hw>Pro*sy"lo*gism</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Pref.
<ets>pro-</ets> + <ets>syllogism</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Logic)</fld> <def>A
syllogism preliminary or logically essential to another syllogism; the
conclusion of such a syllogism, which becomes a premise of the following
syllogism.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Protactic</ent>⟦br⟧
